Class CardType.Builder

    CardType

    public static class CardType.Builder

    Builder for CardType instances.

    You must specify at least one pattern (single number/range) and at least one valid length for the card type.

        public CardType.Builder addSingleNumberPatterns(java.lang.String... patterns)
        Add a set of single number prefixes for the card type. e.g. "1234", "56", "789"

        Calling this method multiple times will add more patterns.

        Parameters:
        patterns - one or more strings of digits
        Returns:
        the builder instance, for method chaining
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if patterns is null, or one or more of the pattern strings is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one or more of the patterns is invalid

      • addRangePatterns

        public CardType.Builder addRangePatterns(java.lang.String... patterns)
        A set of range prefixes for the card type. Each range pattern should consist of the lowest number (inclusive), then a hyphen, then the highest number (also inclusive). e.g. "12-34", "567-890".

        A limitation is that the low and high numbers must have the same number of digits, so a pattern such as "1-20" is considered invalid. If needed, this can be achieved by simply adding 2 patterns - e.g. "1-9" & "10-20".

        Calling this method multiple times will add more patterns.

        Parameters:
        patterns - one or more strings of range patterns
        Returns:
        the builder instance, for method chaining
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if patterns is null, or one or more of the pattern strings is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one or more of the patterns is invalid
